I'm thinking how much I love emus!  So handsome, so attractive, etc.

@Bruce 
Our Thursday average solve time is essentially the same as our Friday time.  Because Thursday trickery it’s average solve time (and therefore the W-Th and Thu-Fri solve times) is not comparable to the other days of the week.  

But we did do those numbers, and W-Th was .1% different. And Th-Fri was 56% different.  Divide the Th-Fri average solve time by 2 (for 2 days), it gives 28%. This indicates the Friday difficulty level is well-calibrated with all the other days of the week, excepting Thursday.

@Ken W 
How interesting!  None of this would have occurred to me, but I could see your (perfectly valid and well-stated) point immediately.  (It almost made me think physical sciences could be interesting...but I recovered quickly!  ha ha, juuuust kidding.  A little.)

Others will say you are a victim of knowing too much, but of course there is no such thing, and I want to thank you for Commenting.  I hope someone on Staff  listens.

@Ken W - Liquids are, indeed, FLUIDS. 

If the clue had said "Liquids, but not gases" or some such thing, then there would be a problem. 

The clue and answer are fine.

